When you see these colors in `get_design_context` output, translate to project tokens:

| Figma MCP Output | Replace With |
|-------------------|-------------|
| `text-[#0b4f75]` | `text-brand-primary` |
| `text-[color:var(--brand-1,#0b4f75)]` | `text-brand-primary` |
| `bg-[#0b4f75]` | `bg-brand-primary` |
| `border-[rgba(11,79,117,0.2)]` | `border-brand-primary-light` |
| `bg-[rgba(11,79,117,0.05)]` | `bg-brand-primary-light-bg` |
| `text-[#717182]` | `text-secondary-text` |
| `bg-[#fffdfc]` | `bg-app-bg-light-gray` |
| `bg-[#f1f6f8]` | `bg-app-bg-item-hover` |
| `text-[#dc2626]` | `text-error` |

For colors NOT in the theme (feature-specific like `#54849E`, `#3A3B44`, etc.), use arbitrary Tailwind values but reference the semantic name in a comment if it maps to a known Figma variable.

## Design Source Traceability

When implementing from Figma, add design source annotations to the file's JSDoc header:

```typescript
/**
 * @file MyScreenView.tsx
 * @description Screen for displaying insights.
 * @figma wxU0NpjXq7hqh1c5G9hGLF node 1141:10586 (My Mind Page)
 */
```

When implementing from a Pencil (.pen) design, use `@pencil` instead:

```typescript
/**
 * @pencil my-design.pen
 * - Desktop: node `abc12` (Frame Name)
 * - Mobile: node `xyz34` (Mobile Frame Name)
 */
```

## Verification Checklist

After implementing a Figma design, verify:

- [ ] Spacing matches Figma (padding, margins, gaps) — use arbitrary values for non-standard sizes
- [ ] Typography matches (font family, size, weight, line-height, letter-spacing)
- [ ] Colors use project tokens where available, arbitrary values with correct hex otherwise
- [ ] Border radius, shadows, and borders match
- [ ] Layout uses flex/grid (never absolute positioning from Figma output)
- [ ] All existing UI components are reused (Button, Badge, Modal, etc.)
- [ ] Icons use Lucide or existing custom SVGs — no new icon packages
- [ ] View/Container split is correct
- [ ] Storybook stories exist for all visual states
- [ ] Design source annotation (`@figma` or `@pencil`) is in the file header
